Interface OptionOptimizePrecompile

All Known Subinterfaces:
CompileOnePerm.CompileOnePermOptions, CompilePerms.CompilePermsOptions, CompilerOptions, DevMode.HostedModeOptions, DevModeBase.HostedModeBaseOptions, HostedModeOptions, JJSOptions, LegacyCompilerOptions, PrecompileOnePerm.PrecompileOnePermOptions, PrecompileTaskOptions
All Known Implementing Classes:
DevMode.HostedModeOptionsImpl, DevModeBase.HostedModeBaseOptionsImpl, JJSOptionsImpl
public interface OptionOptimizePrecompile

Option to early optimize the unified AST during a precompile. Does not correspond to any command line option. This is used directly by compiler clients to specify whether or not to optimize early.

Method Summary
 boolean isOptimizePrecompile()
          Returns true if the compiler should lightly optimize the raw AST before any permutation work.
